22.8:
Then the earth shook and trembled;
the foundations of heaven quaked and reeled—
because he was angry.

22.31:
This God—his way is perfect.
The word of the LORD is proved true;
he is a shield to all who shelter in him.

22.43:
I ground them fine as the dust of the earth;
crushed them, stamped them down
like mud in the streets.

22.44:
You saved me from the strife of my own people;
you made me the head of nations.
Peoples I never knew came to serve me.

22.49:
who brought me out from my enemies.
You raised me above those who rose against me;
you rescued me from the violent man.

22.51:
Great victories he gives to his king;
he shows covenant faithfulness to his anointed—
to David and his seed, forever.
